  "texts": [
    "First, our natural experiment examining GitHub Copilot's selective language support demonstrates that LLMs can also significantly boost voluntary contributions in collaborative environments, one of the earliest works to demonstrate the same.",
    "Second, we find that in voluntary collaborative contexts, LLMs disproportionately enhance iterative innovation over capability innovation due to fundamental differences in contextual requirements and human input.",
    "Iterative tasks leverage LLMs' strengths in contextual understanding by providing existing code as a reference.",
    "This makes LLMs especially effective for tasks with well-defined solution spaces, such as understanding customer concerns, verifying data accuracy, or retrieving relevant documents from large collections.",
    "However, their impact may be more modest, though still valuable, for tasks requiring higher-level abstraction, such as complex system design."
  ],
